There is nothing like fresh Xinjiang 'nang' flatbread early in the morning, particularly when it's straight out of the wood-burning brick oven. Xiaobei Metro, China Guangzhou. 
If you're muslim planning to visit China, Guangzhou anytime soon without the help of a tour agent. Food might be on your worry list.

Here's a free tip:

Xiaobei metro, is also known as Guangzhou Arab Muslim street. Here, you can find countless restaurant selling halal food, from Pakistani cuisine, Somalia cuisine, Xinjiang Muslim, Turkish and Mediterranean cuisine.

Cross over the bridge, behind the train tracks hide an alley full of bbq street food and local eateries at local price.

The one and only, 
Halal Thai Restaurant China, Guangzhou.

3.6.2017 || Guangzhou has some 16,000 African residents making it the largest African settlement in Asia. Most migrants came to the city during the economic boom in the early 2000's seeking out business opportunities, though since then the numbers have been declining due to tougher immigration enforcement and less demand for Chinese goods in Africa. I headed over to "Chocolate City" because I heard that the best chance for me to find some size 13 shoes would be here. It was a cool neighborhood to explore but I left empty handed. If you have a second check Xiaobeilu.org for a photo series in Chocolate city.

LIttle Africa - in the center of Guangzhou there is a little area called chocolate city. Where there are thousands and thousands of Africans doing business and living in Guangzhou. It's one of the most fascinating places in the city. You can go and have Ghana food and get your hair cut in a African beauty salon, purchase Nigerian DVD movies.  When you look behind the scenes you will see there is huge business being conducted in this area with all sorts of products being exported to all areas of Africa.  Doors, windows, clothing, generators, makeup, beauty products, clothing, shoes and more. China is the manufacturing capital of the world and this is where Africa meets China.  In this area the Chinese, blacks and Arabs all mix together, do business together and eat together.  Additionally there are tons of African children who were born and lived all their lives here in China who run around playing in the street speaking pure Chinese with their Chinese friends.
